BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
OHIO (THE SENATE CONCURRING):
WHEREAS, In September 2025, the outstanding public debt of 5
the United States totaled more than $37 trillion, with public 6
debt equaling 123% of gross domestic product, and the debt owed 7
per citizen rising to $108,000; and 8
WHEREAS, More than $8 trillion of the federal debt is owned 9
by individuals not located in the United States, including more 10
than $800 billion owned by individuals in China; and 11
WHEREAS, In fiscal year 2024, the United States had a 12
deficit of over $1 trillion after the United States Congress 13
failed to pass a balanced budget, and federal tax receipts 14
totaled $5 trillion, short of the federal outlays totaling $6.75 15
trillion; and 16
WHEREAS, The Social Security and Medicare Boards of 17
Trustees project that the Old-Age and Survivors Insurance Trust 18

